name: FlutterSoundHelper
desc:
FlutterSoundHelper class is for handleing audio files and buffers.
Most of those utilities use FFmpeg, so are not available in the LITE flavor of Flutter Sound.

name: FlutterSoundHelper
desc: The factory which returns the Singleton

name: logger
desc: The FlutterSoundHelper Logger

name: pcmToWave
desc: Converts a raw PCM file to a WAVE file.

name: pcmToWaveBuffer
desc: Convert a raw PCM buffer to a WAVE buffer.

name: waveToPCM
desc: Convert a WAVE file to a Raw PCM file.

name: waveToPCMBuffer
desc: Convert a WAVE buffer to a Raw PCM buffer.

name: FlutterSoundPlayer
desc: A Player is an object that can playback from various sources.

name: FlutterSoundPlayer
desc:
Instanciate a new Flutter Sound player.
The optional paramater Level logLevel specify the Logger Level you are interested by.
The optional parameter bool voiceProcessing is used to activate the VoiceProcessingIO AudioUnit (only for iOS)

name: closePlayer
desc: Close an open session.

name: dispositionStream
desc:
Provides a stream of dispositions which
provide updated position and duration
as the audio is played.

name: feedFromStream
desc: Used when you want to play live PCM data synchronously.

name: foodSink
desc: The sink side of the Food Controller

name: getPlayerState
desc: Query the current state to the Tau Core layer.

name: getProgress
desc: Get the current progress of a playback.

name: getResourcePath
desc: Get the resource path.

name: isDecoderSupported
desc: Returns true if the specified decoder is supported by flutter_sound on this platform

name: isOpen
desc: Return true if the Player has been open

name: isPaused
desc: Test the Player State

name: isPlaying
desc: Test the Player State

name: isStopped
desc: Test the Player State

name: logger
desc: The FlutterSoundPlayerLogger Logger getter

name: onProgress
desc: The stream side of the Food Controller

name: openPlayer
desc: Open the Player.

name: pausePlayer
desc: Pause the current playback.

name: playerState
desc: The current state of the Player

name: resumePlayer
desc: Resume the current playback.

name: seekToPlayer
desc: To seek to a new location.

name: setLogLevel
desc:
Used if the App wants to dynamically change the Log Level.
Seldom used. Most of the time the Log Level is specified during the constructor.

name: setSpeed
desc: Change the playback speed

name: setSubscriptionDuration
desc: Specify the callbacks frenquency, before calling startPlayer.

name: setVolume
desc: Change the output volume

name: startPlayer
desc: Used to play a sound.

name: startPlayerFromMic
desc: Starts the Microphone and plays what is recorded.

name: startPlayerFromStream
desc: Used to play something from a Dart stream

name: stopPlayer
desc: Stop a playback.

name: FlutterSoundRecorder
desc: A Recorder is an object that can playback from various sources.

name: FlutterSoundRecorder
desc:
Instanciate a new Flutter Sound Recorder.
The optional paramater Level logLevel specify the Logger Level you are interested by.

name: closeRecorder
desc: Close a Recorder

name: deleteRecord
desc: Delete a temporary file

name: getRecordURL
desc: Get the URI of a recorded file.

name: getSampleRate
desc: Get the sampleRate used by startRecorder()

name: isEncoderSupported
desc: Returns true if the specified encoder is supported by flutter_sound on this platform.

name: isPaused
desc: True if recorderState.isPaused

name: isRecording
desc: True if recorderState.isRecording

name: isStopped
desc: True if recorderState.isStopped

name: logger
desc: The FlutterSoundRecorder Logger getter

name: onProgress
desc:
A stream on which FlutterSound will post the recorder progression.
You may listen to this Stream to have feedback on the current recording.

name: openRecorder
desc: Open a Recorder

name: pauseRecorder
desc: Pause the recorder

name: recorderState
desc: The current state of the Recorder

name: resumeRecorder
desc: Resume a paused Recorder

name: setLogLevel
desc:
Used if the App wants to dynamically change the Log Level.
Seldom used. Most of the time the Log Level is specified during the constructor.

name: setSubscriptionDuration
desc:
Sets the frequency at which duration updates are sent to
duration listeners.

name: startRecorder
desc: startRecorder() starts recording with an open session.

name: stopRecorder
desc: Stop a record.

name: Food
desc:
Food is an abstract class which represents objects that can be sent
to a player when playing data from astream or received by a recorder
when recording to a Dart Stream.

name: dummy
desc: use internally by Flutter Sound

name: exec
desc: use internally by Flutter Sound

name: FoodData
desc:
FoodData are the regular objects received from a recorder when recording to a Dart Stream
or sent to a player when playing from a Dart Stream

name: FoodData
desc: The constructor, specifying the data to be sent or that has been received

name: data
desc: the data to be sent (or received)

name: exec
desc: Used internally by Flutter Sound

name: FoodEvent
desc:
foodEvent is a special kind of food which allows to re-synchronize a stream
with a player that play from a Dart Stream

name: FoodEvent
desc: The constructor, specifying the callback which must be fired when synchronization is done

name: exec
desc: Used internally by Flutter Sound

name: on
desc: The callback to fire when this food is synchronized with the player

and postion as 0.

name: duration
desc: The duration of the media.

name: position
desc:
The current position within the media
that we are playing.
